<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Tech Politics — Topic Radar · {{ date }}</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #f7f7f5; --panel: #ffffff; --ink: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b;
    --line: #e6e6e2; --accent: #b4532a; --accent-soft: #f0e2da;
    --good: #2f7d5b; --bad: #b23b3b; --neutral: #6b6b6b; --bar: #e6e6e2;
    --emerging: #8a5cb8; --emerging-soft: #ece2f5;
    --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.05), 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root {
      --bg: #14140f; --panel: #1d1d18; --ink: #ece9e2; --muted: #a09a8e;
      --line: #2c2c25; --accent: #e0824f; --accent-soft: #322019;
      --good: #6cc79a; --bad: #e07a7a; --neutral: #a09a8e; --bar: #2c2c25;
      --emerging: #c9a3ec; --emerging-soft: #2a1f36;
      --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.3), 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.3);
    }
  }
  :root[data-theme="dark"] {
    --bg: #14140f; --panel: #1d1d18; --ink: #ece9e2; --muted: #a09a8e;
    --line: #2c2c25; --accent: #e0824f; --accent-soft: #322019;
    --good: #6cc79a; --bad: #e07a7a; --neutral: #a09a8e; --bar: #2c2c25;
    --emerging: #c9a3ec; --emerging-soft: #2a1f36;
  }
  :root[data-theme="light"] {
    --bg: #f7f7f5; --panel: #ffffff; --ink: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b;
    --line: #e6e6e2; --accent: #b4532a; --accent-soft: #f0e2da;
    --good: #2f7d5b; --bad: #b23b3b; --neutral: #6b6b6b; --bar: #e6e6e2;
    --emerging: #8a5cb8; --emerging-soft: #ece2f5;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--ink);
    font: 16px/1.55 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px 72px; }
  header { margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .kicker { font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; }
  h1 { font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.15; margin: 6px 0 4px; letter-spacing: -.01em; }
  .sub { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; }
  a { color: var(--accent); }
  h2 { font-size: 20px; margin: 36px 0 4px; }
  .section-note { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
  @media (max-width: 680px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .col-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }
  .topic {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 14px 16px; margin: 0 0 10px; box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }
  .topic-top { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px; }
  .topic-label { font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; }
  .topic-count { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); white-space: nowrap; }
  .topic-desc { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 4px; }
  .badge {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .04em;
    text-transform: uppercase; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 6px; margin-right: 6px;
  }
  .badge.new { background: var(--emerging-soft); color: var(--emerging); }
  .badge.emerging { background: var(--emerging-soft); color: var(--emerging); }
  .examples { margin: 8px 0 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
  .examples li { font-size: 12px; margin: 3px 0; }
  .examples a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .examples a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .emerging-card {
    background: var(--emerging-soft); border: 1px solid var(--emerging); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px 18px; margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .emerging-card .topic-label { color: var(--emerging); }
  .baseline-note {
    text-align: center; color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; padding: 28px 16px;
    border: 1px dashed var(--line); border-radius: 12px;
  }
  .empty { text-align: center; color: var(--muted); padding: 40px 0; }
  footer { margin-top: 40px; text-align: center; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
</style>
<script>
  window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">
  <header>
    <div class="kicker">Tech Politics Brief</div>
    <h1>Topic Radar</h1>
    <div class="sub">{{ date }} · generated {{ generated_at }} · extractor: {{ extractor }} · <a href="index.html">← Daily Top 5</a></div>
  </header>

  <h2>🔍 Hidden &amp; emerging</h2>
  {% if not has_baseline %}
  <div class="baseline-note">
    Building trend history — this needs a few days of runs before "emerging" is meaningful.
    Check back after about a week.
  </div>
  {% elif emerging %}
  <div class="section-note">Above their own trailing average, but not yet among today's biggest stories.</div>
  {% for t in emerging %}
  <div class="emerging-card">
    <div class="topic-top">
      <div><span class="badge {{ t.trend }}">{{ t.trend }}</span><span class="topic-label">{{ t.label }}</span></div>
      <div class="topic-count">{{ t.mentions }} mention{{ 's' if t.mentions != 1 else '' }}{% if t.baseline_avg %} · baseline {{ t.baseline_avg }}{% endif %}</div>
    </div>
    {% if t.description %}<div class="topic-desc">{{ t.description }}</div>{% endif %}
    {% if t.examples %}
    <ul class="examples">
      {% for ex in t.examples %}<li><a href="{{ ex.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ ex.title }}</a> — {{ ex.source_name }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">Nothing cleared the emerging bar today — everything is either established or too quiet.</div>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>📊 What's being discussed</h2>
  <div class="section-note">Ranked by mention count today, split by where the coverage is coming from.</div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div>
      <div class="col-title">🇪🇺 Europe</div>
      {% for t in europe %}
      <div class="topic">
        <div class="topic-top">
          <span class="topic-label">{{ t.label }}</span>
          <span class="topic-count">{{ t.europe_count }}</span>
        </div>
        {% if t.description %}<div class="topic-desc">{{ t.description }}</div>{% endif %}
      </div>
      {% else %}
      <div class="empty">No European-tagged topics today.</div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="col-title">🌍 Worldwide</div>
      {% for t in worldwide %}
      <div class="topic">
        <div class="topic-top">
          <span class="topic-label">{{ t.label }}</span>
          <span class="topic-count">{{ t.worldwide_count }}</span>
        </div>
        {% if t.description %}<div class="topic-desc">{{ t.description }}</div>{% endif %}
      </div>
      {% else %}
      <div class="empty">No worldwide-tagged topics today.</div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    Open-vocabulary topics discovered across the full cluster pool, not just the Top 5 · region assigned from article content.
  </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
